    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-12-07T08:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-12-07T08:00:00-05:00" n="716"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d716">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">840.48 Refugees/12–744: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Huddle</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bern</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-12-07T14:00:00+01:00"
                            >December 7, 1944—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 7:33 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>7973. Your 3435, October 6, WRB 198. Foreign Office note November 25 quoted
                    Hungarian response delivered Swiss Legation Budapest November 8. Following is
                    substance note:</p>
                <p>Jewish workers needed within framework Hungary’s total war mobilization.
                    Concentration Jews fit for work not discriminatory as on basis law 1939 all
                    physically fit persons without distinction race nationality or religion subject
                    military labor service under military discipline. Concentration Jews work camps
                    can not be considered as punishment camps. Actually Hungarian and German
                    Governments have consented visit Intercross delegate camps where Hungarian Jews
                    performing labor in Germany. Furthermore the protection of these Jews is
                    appropriately provided for according to nature of work performed.</p>
                <p>Solution of Jewish question Hungary decided solely in light interests Hungary.
                    Foreign threats of whatever kind cannot change this principle. Jewish workers
                    represent part all Hungarian workers and are used within framework Hungarian war
                    effort in a form which appears appropriate Hungarian Government.</p>
                <p>Government intends treat Jews in just and humane manner. Such measures depend,
                    however, upon attitude Jews themselves and upon whether further enemy
                    terroristic attacks on Hungarian civilian population <pb facs="1196" n="1182"
                        xml:id="pg_1182"/> occur since these provoke increased opposition Hungarian
                    population. General standard life Jews will not be lower than working
                    classes.</p>
                <p>Regarding issuance passports and other documentation by Foreign Mission Budapest
                    to Hungarian Jews for their emigration neutral countries or Palestine, Hungarian
                    Government reiterates it is still prepared to recognize these papers and accord
                    emigration Jews concerned within frame-work number visas agreed upon by German
                    Government for transit through German territory in case normal diplomatic
                    relations with interested country so permit.</p>
                <p>Despatch follows.<note n="51" xml:id="d716fn51">Despatch 10132, December 6, not
                        printed.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Huddle</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
